    <p> In the morning I decided to take a look at the hot springs in Taupo and maybe go swimming in it. According to the tourist information and some websites, there should be 2 sources in Tapo. One where you have to pay and the second is free of charge. So I preferred to go to the free. Sam also wanted to come along right away. So we drove there. The sources are even well signposted to the parking lot. But unfortunately no longer. </p>
    <p> After walking around the area for about an hour and yet found only a small stream that looked like warm water, we decided to let it be and make our way. After all, we still had 3 volcanoes to visit and drive over several mountain passes. </p>
    <p> Shortly after Taupo, the route started to become more difficult. She walked many km along steep cliffs above a huge lake before going to the mountains. In the mountains we saw the first volcano of the day (Tongario). Only from a long time but closer to this I didn't necessarily want to. This volcano was just active and broke out just a few weeks earlier. </p>
