    <p> Then it went across a huge level. Always the 3 volcanoes on the left of us. At the second volcano we already dared to take our foot and hoped for a few good photos. This volcano and the plane in front of it have become known through the film Lord of the Rings. The area is in the film Mordor and the volcano is the ring in the film in the film in the Frodo. We were told that some people buy such a ring for $ 100 (65 &euro;), hike up the volcano and throw the ring into it. You have to say that the volcano is not active and covered by snow. Well if you think. </p>
    <p> At the third and highest volcano of the day (FLUMAPEU) we went to everything and drove as far as possible. At the base station at a height of 1630m, driving was over. Up there we drove a few meters through already melting snow. Unfortunately, we did not go up the mountain because the chair lifts were no longer in operation. We didn't feel like it on foot, because it was very cold and the summit was more over 1000m higher. </p>
    <p> We would rather decide to make lunch at the foot of the mountain with more pleasant temperatures. I found a parking lot near a very nice waterfall, which we visit in front of the food. </p>
